
[1]midway

   MID'WAY, n. The middle of the way or distance.

   Paths indirect, or in the midway faint.

    MID'WAY, a. Being in the middle of the way or distance; as the midway
                                    air.

        MID'WAY, adv. In the middle of the way or distance; half way.

   She met his glance midway.
